<p>It seems absurdly basic, but I keep getting errors linking to any page other than index.php from within my site. For example, </p>  <pre><code>&lt;p&gt;No thanks, return to the &lt;a href="index.php"&gt;home page&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; </code></pre>  <p>works perfectly fine and loads the <code>http://example.com/index.php</code> page when clicked. However, both </p>  <pre><code>&lt;p&gt;No thanks, return to the &lt;a href="thankyou.php"&gt;home page&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and </p>  <pre><code>&lt;p&gt;No thanks, return to the &lt;a href="http://example.com/thankyou.php"&gt;home page&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; </code></pre>  <p>result in an error* when clicked, even though I can go enter the address <code>http://example.com/thankyou.php</code> directly in a browser address bar and it loads perfectly.</p>  <p>*The error message is:</p>  <pre><code>Invalid query: You have an error in your SQL syntax; check the manual that corresponds to your MySQL server version for the right syntax to use near '( ID int NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, PRIMARY KEY(ID), timestamp int NOT NU' at line 1 </code></pre>